ths from coronavirus were reported, bringing the country death toll to 49.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213525/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 49 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 82 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-03-31|website=CNN.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref> Twenty of the cases are aboard a passenger ship stationed out of the port of Piraeus. It carried 382 persons, including 36 Greeks, 150 Turks, 83 Indonesians and others. At least some of the persons were Turkish workers travelling to Spain but the ship was turned back to Turkey when the cases were identified. It was not accepted in Turkey and since 21st of March is at Piraeus.<ref>[https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-karantina-peiraia-kroyazieroploio \"Coronavirus: In quarantine at Piraeus the cruiser 'El. Venizelos' with the 20 cases\", iefimerida, 31-3-2020]</ref>\n\n=== April ===\n\n*On 1 April, 101 new cases were confirmed in Greece, bringing the country total to 1415. One more death from coronavirus was reported, bringing the country death toll to 50.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/213658/koronoios-live-oi-anakoinoseis-tsiodra-xardalia|title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 50 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03bd\u03b5\u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03af \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b1\u03c2 - 1.415 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1|last=Newsroom|date=2020-04-01|website=cnn.gr|language=el|access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\n==Statistics==\n\n===COVID-19 Cases in Greece===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Date\n!Confirmed\nNew \n!Deaths\nNew\n!Confirmed\n\nTotal \n!Deaths\nTota